WEBVTT

1
00:00:14.389 --> 00:00:16.391
[water babbling]

2
00:00:18.768 --> 00:00:20.979
[birdsong]

3
00:00:22.731 --> 00:00:24.733
[light snoring]

4
00:00:45.628 --> 00:00:47.213
[imitating horse snorting]

5
00:00:51.342 --> 00:00:54.554
-[♪ string music playing]
-[horse squealing]

6
00:01:02.062 --> 00:01:04.272
-[horse squealing]
-Easy. boy.

7
00:01:14.324 --> 00:01:17.494
[♪ dramatic string music
continues playing]

8
00:01:24.876 --> 00:01:27.087
-[birdsong]
-[water lapping]

9
00:01:31.883 --> 00:01:34.636
-[neighing]
-Come on!

10
00:01:34.677 --> 00:01:36.346
Just run!

11
00:01:36.387 --> 00:01:38.640
-Move.
-[horse neighing]

12
00:01:38.681 --> 00:01:40.433
You're stubborn as old iron.

13
00:01:40.475 --> 00:01:42.143
He's twice the size
of your last rider.

14
00:01:42.185 --> 00:01:44.020
and the field could be
just like this or worse.

15
00:01:44.062 --> 00:01:45.855
so you best get
your feet under you.

16
00:01:45.897 --> 00:01:47.649
[nickering]

17
00:01:47.690 --> 00:01:51.069
My father told me you should
never talk to a horse.

18
00:01:51.111 --> 00:01:52.779
He said they're
dumber than dogs

19
00:01:52.821 --> 00:01:54.614
and only
understand the crop.

20
00:01:54.656 --> 00:01:56.241
[snuffling]

21
00:01:58.368 --> 00:02:02.205
[sighs]
But I don't think that's true.

22
00:02:02.205 --> 00:02:05.375
I think a horse doesn't want
to be ordered about

23
00:02:05.375 --> 00:02:07.335
any more than a man does.

24
00:02:09.629 --> 00:02:12.090
Ser Duncan only has us.

25
00:02:12.132 --> 00:02:14.717
And if he loses.
he won't even have that.

26
00:02:15.927 --> 00:02:17.887
I can get the weapon
in his hand...

27
00:02:18.763 --> 00:02:20.431
-somehow.
-[nickering]

28
00:02:21.307 --> 00:02:23.101
But then. it's up to you.

29
00:02:29.732 --> 00:02:32.527
Hyah! Go!

30
00:02:32.569 --> 00:02:34.571
[splatting]

31
00:02:36.865 --> 00:02:38.408
[neighing]

32
00:02:39.367 --> 00:02:42.245
[♪ dramatic string music
playing]

33
00:02:43.955 --> 00:02:46.791
Hyah! Yah!

34
00:02:48.668 --> 00:02:50.879
Hyah! Yah!

35
00:02:56.384 --> 00:02:57.343
Not bad.

36
00:02:57.385 --> 00:02:59.804
Ha! Go!

37
00:02:59.846 --> 00:03:01.764
Go. Thunder!

38
00:03:01.764 --> 00:03:03.766
[sheep bleating]

39
00:03:07.270 --> 00:03:09.189
Ser Duncan. take it.

40
00:03:09.898 --> 00:03:11.733
Ha! Go. Thunder!

41
00:03:13.109 --> 00:03:14.777
[horse neighing]

42
00:03:18.364 --> 00:03:19.741
Take it quick.
Ser Duncan.

43
00:03:19.782 --> 00:03:21.534
Go. Thunder!

44
00:03:21.576 --> 00:03:23.786
-[horse neighing]
-[Egg] Whoo!

45
00:03:23.828 --> 00:03:25.997
Come on!

46
00:03:26.039 --> 00:03:29.876
Whoo!

47
00:03:29.918 --> 00:03:33.296
Good boy.
Good boy. Thunder.

48
00:03:33.296 --> 00:03:35.298
-Good boy.
-[Thunder nickering]

49
00:03:35.340 --> 00:03:37.300
You steal that horse?

50
00:03:50.313 --> 00:03:53.274
Tell the truth.
We'll be fair.

51
00:03:53.316 --> 00:03:56.402
It's not stealing if you
mean to put it back.

52
00:03:59.322 --> 00:04:01.241
[Thunder whinnying]

53
00:04:04.994 --> 00:04:07.705
[Egg shushing]

54
00:04:12.252 --> 00:04:13.878
What's wrong with your hair?

55
00:04:13.920 --> 00:04:15.880
What's wrong with your eye?

56
00:04:17.966 --> 00:04:19.634
[horse whinnying]

57
00:04:20.843 --> 00:04:22.220
[crowd groaning]

58
00:04:23.012 --> 00:04:24.097
Ahh!

59
00:04:24.138 --> 00:04:27.225
[shouting]

60
00:04:30.353 --> 00:04:32.522
You're Ser Robyn Rhysling.

61
00:04:32.563 --> 00:04:35.400
You're the maddest knight
in the Seven Kingdoms.

62
00:04:35.441 --> 00:04:37.819
We are a vessel
for the Warrior.

63
00:04:37.860 --> 00:04:42.365
When it is madness bid.
it is madness delivered.

64
00:04:43.366 --> 00:04:45.076
You're small for a squire.

65
00:04:45.118 --> 00:04:48.037
I serve Ser Duncan the Tall.

66
00:04:48.079 --> 00:04:50.331
He's large enough
for the both of us.

67
00:04:51.624 --> 00:04:54.377
-We've not heard of him.
-You will.

68
00:04:55.962 --> 00:04:57.964
[birdsong]

69
00:04:59.215 --> 00:05:01.551
[Thunder neighing]

70
00:05:10.977 --> 00:05:12.770
Where have you been?

71
00:05:12.812 --> 00:05:14.022
[Egg] Training.

72
00:05:15.732 --> 00:05:17.817
Don't wander off
without telling me.

73
00:05:22.447 --> 00:05:24.699
What are you doing. Ser?

74
00:05:24.741 --> 00:05:27.827
-Sewing a patch.
-Is that not my job?

75
00:05:28.870 --> 00:05:30.079
You know how?

76
00:05:33.374 --> 00:05:34.917
Then quit jawing
and get the brushes.

77
00:05:34.917 --> 00:05:38.004
Thunder looks like he's been
dragged through a hedge.

78
00:05:38.046 --> 00:05:39.255
What about breakfast?

79
00:05:39.297 --> 00:05:41.424
There's salt beef
after you're done.

80
00:05:42.342 --> 00:05:43.718
I'd sooner eat
the horse. ser.

81
00:05:43.760 --> 00:05:46.471
You'll eat my fist
if you don't do as you're told.

82
00:05:55.813 --> 00:05:57.607
Never mind that.

83
00:05:58.441 --> 00:06:00.651
Yeah.
Yeah. just like that.

84
00:06:00.693 --> 00:06:04.113
Keep it as close to the edge
as possible.

85
00:06:04.113 --> 00:06:05.573
And that's your whipstitch.

86
00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:07.825
How'd you get it so even?

87
00:06:09.327 --> 00:06:11.287
Just. like--
just practice.

88
00:06:11.329 --> 00:06:12.955
Just try again.

89
00:06:16.793 --> 00:06:18.669
-There.
-Yes!

90
00:06:21.172 --> 00:06:23.007
-Ser?
-Mm-hmm?

91
00:06:23.049 --> 00:06:25.676
Is it odd that I have black hair
growing out of my stones?

92
00:06:25.718 --> 00:06:27.762
It's odd that you're telling me.

93
00:06:30.431 --> 00:06:33.309
[singing] ♪ Prince Baelor
was the first born ♪

94
00:06:33.309 --> 00:06:35.478
♪ Prince Maekar
sprang out last ♪

95
00:06:35.478 --> 00:06:38.523
-[Dunk retching]
-♪ Daemon was the bastard.
so they kicked his bastard ♪

96
00:06:38.564 --> 00:06:42.068
♪ Grass is green in summer.
green grass I adore ♪

97
00:06:42.110 --> 00:06:45.571
-[Dunk vomiting]
-♪ But grass is red all over
when you kill a rebel ♪

98
00:06:45.613 --> 00:06:47.365
-♪ Horses die in battle ♪
-[Drunk groaning]

99
00:06:47.407 --> 00:06:49.158
♪ This battle was the front ♪

100
00:06:49.200 --> 00:06:52.703
♪ Blackfyre's not a trueborn.
he came from the wrong ♪

101
00:06:52.745 --> 00:06:56.207
♪ Country was in peril.
The Anvil was a rock ♪

102
00:06:56.249 --> 00:06:59.585
♪ The Hammer
smashed the bastard
with his giant veiny ♪

103
00:06:59.627 --> 00:07:03.714
-♪ Host of Dornish spearmen ♪
-It's time.

104
00:07:05.174 --> 00:07:07.385
-Fetch my armor.
-Now?

105
00:07:09.387 --> 00:07:11.431
Aye. now.

106
00:07:11.472 --> 00:07:12.682
[Egg] Why?

107
00:07:14.225 --> 00:07:16.352
Because I mean
to enter the lists.

108
00:07:16.394 --> 00:07:18.396
You don't have your shield.

109
00:07:19.188 --> 00:07:21.357
[sheep bleating]

110
00:07:21.399 --> 00:07:23.651
We'll-- yeah. we'll gather it
along the way.

111
00:07:23.693 --> 00:07:24.777
-[sniffling]
-Mm-hmm.

112
00:07:24.819 --> 00:07:26.571
Also. the right
of the first challenge

113
00:07:26.612 --> 00:07:28.114
goes to knights of high birth
and renown.

114
00:07:28.156 --> 00:07:31.367
Are you a knight
of high birth and renown. ser?

115
00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:35.455
Wait. so I-- I cannot
enter the lists today?

116
00:07:35.496 --> 00:07:36.873
[Egg] Not today. ser. no.

117
00:07:36.873 --> 00:07:40.001
Only knights of high birth
and renown.

118
00:07:41.836 --> 00:07:44.380
Then why have I been
vomiting all morning?

119
00:07:44.422 --> 00:07:45.882
It's a mystery.

120
00:07:45.923 --> 00:07:47.925
[goose honking]

121
00:07:52.555 --> 00:07:54.056
[Dunk] No. no. no. no. no.

122
00:07:54.098 --> 00:07:56.976
Um. uh. goose eggs.

123
00:07:57.018 --> 00:07:58.978
Just-- just the eggs.

124
00:07:59.020 --> 00:08:00.646
No. no. no. uh...

125
00:08:00.688 --> 00:08:04.609
Shit. um.
goose eggs. like...

126
00:08:04.650 --> 00:08:06.986
-Just the...
-[townsfolk chattering]

127
00:08:08.196 --> 00:08:09.989
Thank you.

128
00:08:12.575 --> 00:08:15.453
Do you like goose eggs?

129
00:08:15.495 --> 00:08:18.498
Your shield will be ready
this evening. ser.

130
00:08:20.458 --> 00:08:21.834
Th-Thank you.

131
00:08:21.876 --> 00:08:23.878
[donkey braying]

132
00:08:31.928 --> 00:08:33.262
[rooster crowing]

133
00:08:33.304 --> 00:08:36.766
-[Egg] Ooh. ooh! Ooh!
-Shut up.

134
00:08:37.683 --> 00:08:41.020
[♪ soft music playing]

135
00:08:41.062 --> 00:08:44.065
[♪ cheerful whistling]

136
00:09:03.543 --> 00:09:04.877
[Egg] Mm!

137
00:09:08.089 --> 00:09:09.298
Mm!

138
00:09:11.384 --> 00:09:13.594
[crowd roaring]

139
00:09:14.303 --> 00:09:16.138
Come on!

140
00:09:16.180 --> 00:09:19.642
-Come on! Whoo!
-Whoo!

141
00:09:21.352 --> 00:09:22.979
-Why not?
-Come on!

142
00:09:24.063 --> 00:09:26.148
[laughing]

143
00:09:26.190 --> 00:09:28.192
[coughing]

144
00:09:30.152 --> 00:09:32.154
[jouster shouting]

145
00:09:33.573 --> 00:09:36.659
-[crowd roaring]
-Come on!

146
00:09:37.785 --> 00:09:38.995
Whoo!

147
00:09:40.121 --> 00:09:41.664
[applause]

148
00:09:41.664 --> 00:09:44.166
[mimicking Dunk]
Do you want
some hard salt beef?

149
00:09:47.086 --> 00:09:49.922
[in high-pitched voice]
Oh. I'm Egg. I can't
eat hard salt beef.

150
00:09:49.964 --> 00:09:53.551
I just eat lovely food
and grapes and all the...

151
00:09:53.593 --> 00:09:54.844
[babbling]

152
00:09:54.885 --> 00:09:56.554
Can't even drink
a pint of ale.

153
00:09:56.596 --> 00:09:59.056
Yeah. 'cause it's disgusting.

154
00:09:59.098 --> 00:10:01.475
-It's not disgusting.
-Yes. it is disgusting.

155
00:10:01.517 --> 00:10:02.852
-It's not disgusting.
-It's disgusting.

156
00:10:02.893 --> 00:10:04.312
Well. then I won't buy you
another one.

157
00:10:04.353 --> 00:10:06.230
-Good.
-[sighs]

158
00:10:09.191 --> 00:10:12.028
[Egg]
I think I could be quite
happy in a place like this.

159
00:10:13.779 --> 00:10:15.865
[Dunk]
You're in a place like this.

160
00:10:15.906 --> 00:10:19.243
-I meant for a while.
-Ah. yeah.

161
00:10:20.453 --> 00:10:23.247
[Egg] After I lead a great
campaign for my lord. of course.

162
00:10:23.289 --> 00:10:24.665
Of course.

163
00:10:25.708 --> 00:10:28.252
I return a war hero
and he gives me

164
00:10:28.294 --> 00:10:30.129
a parcel of land
for my very own.

165
00:10:30.171 --> 00:10:33.591
and the hand of his second
most beautiful daughter.

166
00:10:33.633 --> 00:10:35.968
Second most?

167
00:10:36.010 --> 00:10:39.221
Well. you've already
married the first most.

168
00:10:39.221 --> 00:10:40.973
Have you not. ser?

169
00:10:41.849 --> 00:10:43.726
[crowd cheering in distance]

170
00:10:43.726 --> 00:10:47.063
[Egg] I'd keep horses.
plant oats and peas.

171
00:10:47.063 --> 00:10:49.857
-Raise cows.
-And lambs. perhaps.

172
00:10:49.899 --> 00:10:51.651
-Fuck your lambs.
-[chuckles]

173
00:10:51.692 --> 00:10:53.903
Did you really ride
all the way here

174
00:10:53.944 --> 00:10:55.780
in the back
of some farmer's wagon?

175
00:10:55.821 --> 00:10:57.657
I don't want
to talk about it.

176
00:10:57.698 --> 00:10:59.241
[snickering]

177
00:11:05.831 --> 00:11:07.375
I'll say this for you.

178
00:11:08.918 --> 00:11:10.920
You're a good worker
when you put your mind to it.

179
00:11:10.920 --> 00:11:12.338
Think so?

180
00:11:13.631 --> 00:11:14.924
Mm-hmm.

181
00:11:18.260 --> 00:11:21.597
Does that mean
I can stay on as your squire

182
00:11:21.639 --> 00:11:23.683
after the tournament?

183
00:11:29.605 --> 00:11:30.981
If I lose my first joust.

184
00:11:31.023 --> 00:11:33.818
I'll scarcely be a knight
after the tournament.

185
00:11:37.697 --> 00:11:39.281
But if you win?

186
00:11:47.123 --> 00:11:48.290
If I win...

187
00:11:53.879 --> 00:11:55.715
If I win. you can--

188
00:11:55.756 --> 00:11:57.633
Ser Duncan?

189
00:11:57.633 --> 00:11:59.510
A word. if you please.

190
00:11:59.552 --> 00:12:01.595
[hocking phlegm]

191
00:12:01.637 --> 00:12:03.055
[spitting]

192
00:12:07.143 --> 00:12:08.978
Is there an issue
with my entry?

193
00:12:08.978 --> 00:12:12.231
Hm? Oh. no.
No. I. uh...

194
00:12:12.273 --> 00:12:14.942
I only wanted to show you
a new fishing spot I'm keen on.

195
00:12:17.445 --> 00:12:19.822
Uh. Ser Duncan.

196
00:12:19.864 --> 00:12:23.993
I believe we are both
men of honor.

197
00:12:24.034 --> 00:12:26.829
So. I hope you understand
that what I ask

198
00:12:26.871 --> 00:12:29.999
serves no private interest.

199
00:12:29.999 --> 00:12:32.084
Might it surprise you
to learn that my Lord Ashford

200
00:12:32.126 --> 00:12:34.795
has richly overspent
on his daughter's pageant?

201
00:12:36.714 --> 00:12:37.923
-It might not.
-Mm.

202
00:12:37.965 --> 00:12:40.009
Well. with winter
not so long past.

203
00:12:40.050 --> 00:12:42.678
and many
of our flocks collapsed.

204
00:12:42.678 --> 00:12:44.305
hard times lay ahead.

205
00:12:44.346 --> 00:12:48.350
Unless we endeavor
to reverse our fortunes.

206
00:12:49.602 --> 00:12:51.103
[sighs]

207
00:12:51.896 --> 00:12:54.398
I-- I don't have
any money. I...

208
00:12:57.359 --> 00:12:59.403
Shocking. that may be.

209
00:13:00.362 --> 00:13:03.741
I mean not to rob you.
but to reward you.

210
00:13:06.076 --> 00:13:08.204
-[scoffs] Reward me?
-Aye.

211
00:13:08.204 --> 00:13:10.790
What do you know of
Lord Ashford's youngest.

212
00:13:10.831 --> 00:13:12.208
Sir Androw?

213
00:13:15.211 --> 00:13:16.378
[crashing]

214
00:13:16.420 --> 00:13:18.339
[crowd cheering]

215
00:13:22.468 --> 00:13:23.761
He-- he's a deft lance.

216
00:13:23.803 --> 00:13:24.970
-Indeed. indeed.
-Mm.

217
00:13:25.012 --> 00:13:29.850
But were a challenger
to come forth

218
00:13:29.892 --> 00:13:32.686
and unhorse Ser Androw.
against all odds.

219
00:13:32.728 --> 00:13:35.523
the lucky few who backed
such an unlikely winner

220
00:13:35.564 --> 00:13:37.983
would find their pockets full.

221
00:13:43.739 --> 00:13:44.740
Now. now. rest assured.

222
00:13:44.782 --> 00:13:47.201
Rest assured.
I mean no disrespect.

223
00:13:47.243 --> 00:13:49.995
I ask only what
you already intend.

224
00:13:50.037 --> 00:13:51.247
Drive your foe
from his saddle

225
00:13:51.247 --> 00:13:53.249
and take your place
on champion's row.

226
00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:59.088
I do not want a victory
that I have not earned.

227
00:14:00.506 --> 00:14:02.091
Have you not earned it?

228
00:14:05.594 --> 00:14:07.721
Let Ser Androw take the fall.

229
00:14:07.763 --> 00:14:09.098
and you shall have
his horse. arms.

230
00:14:09.098 --> 00:14:11.767
and armor as recompense
for your role.

231
00:14:11.767 --> 00:14:13.143
A tidy sum for
a young hedge knight

232
00:14:13.185 --> 00:14:15.437
who presently calls
an alder tree home.

233
00:14:17.398 --> 00:14:18.566
It's an elm.

234
00:14:20.943 --> 00:14:22.152
[whispering] Elm.

235
00:14:26.115 --> 00:14:27.950
I beg you. think on it.

236
00:14:27.950 --> 00:14:30.119
I shall seek your answer
on the morrow.

237
00:14:32.371 --> 00:14:35.249
Perhaps the rains
will hold till then.

238
00:14:36.667 --> 00:14:38.419
Mind your pride.
Ser Duncan.

239
00:14:43.716 --> 00:14:45.426
[hocking. spitting]

240
00:14:47.970 --> 00:14:50.139
-[water babbling]
-[birdsong]

241
00:14:55.102 --> 00:14:56.687
[sighs]

242
00:14:56.729 --> 00:14:58.939
[horn blowing]

243
00:15:07.156 --> 00:15:08.991
[herald] Son of Meakar.

244
00:15:08.991 --> 00:15:11.160
grandson to King Daeron the Good

245
00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:14.163
and Prince
of House Targaryen.

246
00:15:14.163 --> 00:15:17.666
Prince Aerion Brightflame.

247
00:15:17.708 --> 00:15:19.919
[cheering and applause]

248
00:15:28.260 --> 00:15:30.262
[horn blowing]

249
00:15:32.514 --> 00:15:33.390
Hyah!

250
00:15:33.432 --> 00:15:36.644
-[cheering and applause]
-[metal clanging]

251
00:15:48.739 --> 00:15:50.240
[Aerion Targaryen]
Cousin.

252
00:15:52.034 --> 00:15:55.037
[horns blaring. drums beating]

253
00:15:57.873 --> 00:16:00.584
Not to worry.
I won't embarrass you today.

254
00:16:05.172 --> 00:16:07.091
Come out. come out.
little knight.

255
00:16:08.801 --> 00:16:10.469
It's time you
faced the dragon.

256
00:16:12.429 --> 00:16:14.640
-[grunting] Hyah!
-[cheering and applause]

257
00:16:16.850 --> 00:16:18.519
[horse whinnying]

258
00:16:20.729 --> 00:16:22.398
[shouting]

259
00:16:23.691 --> 00:16:25.693
[cheering and applause continue]

260
00:16:28.570 --> 00:16:30.364
[horse neighing]

261
00:16:33.283 --> 00:16:35.494
[neighing]

262
00:16:35.536 --> 00:16:37.246
[snorting]

263
00:16:40.082 --> 00:16:42.251
[thunder rumbling]

264
00:16:49.425 --> 00:16:52.678
-[jousters] Hyah!
-[cheering and applause]

265
00:16:53.679 --> 00:16:55.973
Kill him. Kill him!

266
00:16:58.434 --> 00:17:00.436
[crowd] Aww!

267
00:17:00.477 --> 00:17:02.479
[crowd booing]

268
00:17:06.817 --> 00:17:08.777
[horse neighing]

269
00:17:08.819 --> 00:17:09.945
[Aerion exclaiming]

270
00:17:09.987 --> 00:17:11.280
Lance!

271
00:17:12.448 --> 00:17:13.449
Go!

272
00:17:18.579 --> 00:17:19.788
He's too low.

273
00:17:21.540 --> 00:17:23.542
[horse squealing]

274
00:17:27.254 --> 00:17:30.382
-[screaming]
-[crowd groaning]

275
00:17:36.346 --> 00:17:38.348
[groaning]

276
00:17:40.601 --> 00:17:42.519
[groaning continues]

277
00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:47.232
[crowd clamoring]

278
00:17:55.616 --> 00:17:57.534
[clamoring continues]

279
00:17:57.576 --> 00:18:01.497
♪♪

280
00:18:02.623 --> 00:18:04.541
[horse neighing]

281
00:18:04.583 --> 00:18:06.585
[clamoring continues]

282
00:18:22.935 --> 00:18:25.145
[horse squealing]

283
00:18:27.898 --> 00:18:30.192
-I want to leave.
-Aye.

284
00:18:31.527 --> 00:18:33.112
[axe thudding]

285
00:18:34.530 --> 00:18:36.532
[thunder rumbling]

286
00:18:37.741 --> 00:18:39.493
That was a terrible sight.

287
00:18:40.410 --> 00:18:42.538
But a squire
must be strong.

288
00:18:42.579 --> 00:18:44.957
A mishap may befall me.
and I'll need you

289
00:18:44.998 --> 00:18:46.708
to keep your wits if it does.

290
00:18:47.709 --> 00:18:49.711
That was no mishap.

291
00:18:49.711 --> 00:18:52.214
[thunder rumbling]

292
00:18:56.009 --> 00:18:58.345
The jousting is done
for the day. I think.

293
00:18:59.388 --> 00:19:00.556
Come. lad.

294
00:19:02.432 --> 00:19:06.186
[singing] ♪ Oh! Alice
was a special lass ♪

295
00:19:06.228 --> 00:19:08.397
♪ Born bereft 'er thumb ♪

296
00:19:08.397 --> 00:19:12.192
♪ Lost a digit tending flock.
now feeling awfully glum ♪

297
00:19:12.234 --> 00:19:14.778
♪ Oh! Alice
with three fingers ♪

298
00:19:14.820 --> 00:19:16.488
♪ A copper in her glass ♪

299
00:19:16.530 --> 00:19:18.365
♪ Had two fingers
less than most ♪

300
00:19:18.407 --> 00:19:20.701
♪ She'll shove them
up your arse. hey! ♪

301
00:19:20.742 --> 00:19:24.079
♪ I once gave her a silver.
feeling down and lone ♪

302
00:19:24.079 --> 00:19:27.708
♪ I tried to buy a pinky.
but I got the whole arm bone ♪

303
00:19:27.749 --> 00:19:31.587
♪ Oh! Alice with three fingers
never had a lot ♪

304
00:19:31.628 --> 00:19:33.589
♪ She gave me
all she had to give ♪

305
00:19:33.589 --> 00:19:35.174
♪ Two more than
what was sought ♪

306
00:19:35.215 --> 00:19:37.092
♪ Oh! Two more than
what I bought ♪

307
00:19:37.134 --> 00:19:39.344
[all cheering]

308
00:19:43.557 --> 00:19:45.559
Do you suppose
there was an Alice. ser?

309
00:19:47.436 --> 00:19:50.397
A crippled girl who shoved
her hand up men's arses?

310
00:19:50.439 --> 00:19:52.274
I think there probably was.

311
00:19:53.192 --> 00:19:54.735
Of course.
there probably was.

312
00:19:55.694 --> 00:19:57.779
Do you think her name
was really Alice?

313
00:20:00.324 --> 00:20:02.326
Mm. no.
I just think Alice

314
00:20:02.367 --> 00:20:04.620
is a nice name
to write a song to.

315
00:20:05.495 --> 00:20:06.914
That means there
was a cripple girl

316
00:20:06.955 --> 00:20:09.374
who was so good
at pleasuring men
in their bums

317
00:20:09.416 --> 00:20:11.793
that they saw fit
to celebrate her in song.

318
00:20:11.835 --> 00:20:14.296
yet they could not bother
credit her true name?

319
00:20:14.296 --> 00:20:16.131
If there's a lesson in that.

320
00:20:16.131 --> 00:20:18.592
it's for wiser men
than me to say.

321
00:20:18.634 --> 00:20:20.594
Perhaps it is
a story of honor.

322
00:20:21.803 --> 00:20:23.639
Honor?

323
00:20:23.639 --> 00:20:26.725
A misfortuned girl making
the best of her natural gifts.

324
00:20:28.060 --> 00:20:30.229
One might wish for more.

325
00:20:30.270 --> 00:20:32.356
But is this not the act
of a dogged spirit?

326
00:20:32.397 --> 00:20:34.191
Giving more
than what is asked?

327
00:20:34.233 --> 00:20:35.984
"The whole arm bone."
as it were.

328
00:20:37.361 --> 00:20:39.363
Perhaps her name
does not matter. then.

329
00:20:39.404 --> 00:20:42.241
It's-- it's her story
that abides.

330
00:20:42.282 --> 00:20:44.326
Her name is Hope. ser.

331
00:20:44.326 --> 00:20:46.453
Belongs to all
who invoke it.

332
00:20:47.663 --> 00:20:51.416
[singing] ♪ Oh! Alice
was a special lass ♪

333
00:20:51.458 --> 00:20:53.460
♪ Born bereft 'er thumb ♪

334
00:20:53.502 --> 00:20:55.337
♪ She lost a digit
tending flock ♪

335
00:20:55.337 --> 00:20:57.005
♪ And now she's awfully-- ♪

336
00:20:57.047 --> 00:20:59.258
-[chicken bawking]
-[donkey braying]

337
00:21:01.551 --> 00:21:03.303
[Dunk]
Did you ever know
your father. Egg?

338
00:21:03.345 --> 00:21:04.846
[Egg] Mm. uh...

339
00:21:06.014 --> 00:21:08.141
No. Not really.

340
00:21:08.183 --> 00:21:10.352
Most like I saw mine hanged.

341
00:21:12.521 --> 00:21:15.107
There was a pot shop
in Flea Bottom.

342
00:21:15.148 --> 00:21:19.319
I used to sell them
rats and cats
and pigeons for brown.

343
00:21:19.361 --> 00:21:21.780
Cook there always said
my father was some thief.

344
00:21:23.365 --> 00:21:24.741
If he was as big as me.

345
00:21:24.783 --> 00:21:27.411
he wouldn't have made
a very good one.

346
00:21:27.452 --> 00:21:29.663
[townsfolk chattering]

347
00:21:39.298 --> 00:21:40.966
Say your fortune.

348
00:21:41.008 --> 00:21:42.884
Oh. yeah.
Go on. then.

349
00:21:42.884 --> 00:21:45.971
You shall know great success
and be richer than a Lannister.

350
00:21:46.930 --> 00:21:48.765
Thank you.
Do the boy now.

351
00:21:52.227 --> 00:21:53.854
You shall be king...

352
00:21:55.230 --> 00:21:56.648
and die in a hot fire.

353
00:21:56.690 --> 00:21:59.359
and worms shall feed
upon your ashes.

354
00:22:00.444 --> 00:22:03.530
And all who know you
shall rejoice in your dying.

355
00:22:04.239 --> 00:22:05.490
What?

356
00:22:07.242 --> 00:22:10.078
[laughing]
Thank you. that's very good.

357
00:22:13.123 --> 00:22:14.666
Why would she say that?

358
00:22:14.708 --> 00:22:17.002
Why would she say what?
Come on.

359
00:22:21.256 --> 00:22:22.632
Ser Duncan!

360
00:22:23.675 --> 00:22:25.260
I saw you earlier
with this boy.

361
00:22:25.302 --> 00:22:28.305
Uh. yeah.
This boy is my squire.

362
00:22:28.347 --> 00:22:31.224
Egg. this is. um.
Raymun Fossoway.

363
00:22:31.266 --> 00:22:33.435
-Good day.
-[people cheering in distance]

364
00:22:33.435 --> 00:22:35.312
See our show!
It's great!

365
00:22:35.354 --> 00:22:37.481
Will you join me in my tent
for a cup of cider?

366
00:22:37.522 --> 00:22:39.858
I could wait
at the puppet show. ser.

367
00:22:39.900 --> 00:22:42.444
and bring your shield
when the performance is over.

368
00:22:45.489 --> 00:22:46.948
We make it ourselves.

369
00:22:49.659 --> 00:22:50.744
Very well.

370
00:22:51.787 --> 00:22:53.997
[people laughing and applauding
in distance]

371
00:22:56.792 --> 00:22:59.002
[Raymun Fossoway]
Have you chosen an opponent yet?

372
00:22:59.044 --> 00:23:00.921
[Dunk] Oh. uh. I'm not sure.

373
00:23:00.962 --> 00:23:02.464
[liquid sloshing]

374
00:23:03.924 --> 00:23:05.967
Who does your cousin
mean to challenge?

375
00:23:05.967 --> 00:23:09.638
[chuckles] If anyone's
wounded on the morrow...

376
00:23:09.638 --> 00:23:11.848
I'm sure Steffon will be quick
to knock on his shield.

377
00:23:13.225 --> 00:23:15.560
He's about as chivalrous
as a starved weasel.

378
00:23:17.813 --> 00:23:19.481
[grunting. sighing]

379
00:23:22.943 --> 00:23:26.405
I suppose Ser Androw and I
are quite equally matched.

380
00:23:26.446 --> 00:23:29.324
A local favorite.
You mean to play the villain?

381
00:23:29.324 --> 00:23:31.159
[chuckles]

382
00:23:31.159 --> 00:23:33.328
I heard Aerion were in
a spittin' rage at Lord Ashford

383
00:23:33.328 --> 00:23:34.663
for giving away his horse.

384
00:23:34.704 --> 00:23:36.832
Little comfort that will be
to Ser Humfrey.

385
00:23:36.873 --> 00:23:38.583
It looked as if he was
going to carry the day.

386
00:23:38.625 --> 00:23:40.127
Now his leg's shattered
like a baking dish.

387
00:23:40.168 --> 00:23:43.922
My squire thinks Aerion meant
to kill the horse. [chuckles]

388
00:23:46.425 --> 00:23:48.301
Just hard to accept
that a knight

389
00:23:48.343 --> 00:23:49.886
might be so dishonorable...

390
00:23:50.971 --> 00:23:52.139
let alone a prince.

391
00:23:52.180 --> 00:23:53.765
Why is that hard?

392
00:23:55.809 --> 00:23:56.643
N-No. I--

393
00:23:56.685 --> 00:23:58.687
They're incestuous aliens.
Duncan.

394
00:23:59.980 --> 00:24:03.108
Blood-magickers and tyrants
who've burned our lands.

395
00:24:03.150 --> 00:24:04.860
enslaved our people.

396
00:24:04.860 --> 00:24:07.070
dragged us into their wars
without a mote of respect

397
00:24:07.112 --> 00:24:08.613
for our history
or our customs.

398
00:24:08.655 --> 00:24:10.323
Every pale-haired brat
they saddled on us

399
00:24:10.365 --> 00:24:12.868
has been madder than the last.
gods know how.

400
00:24:12.868 --> 00:24:15.662
The only honorable thing
a Targaryen

401
00:24:15.704 --> 00:24:18.540
can do for this realm
is finish on his wife's tits.

402
00:24:18.582 --> 00:24:21.209
So aye. I think he meant
to kill the fucking horse.

403
00:24:24.045 --> 00:24:25.589
[Raymun sighs]

404
00:24:29.676 --> 00:24:31.887
I got a bit
carried away there.

405
00:24:31.928 --> 00:24:33.138
[chuckles]

406
00:24:35.807 --> 00:24:38.685
I heard that part
about the tits from Steffon.

407
00:24:43.773 --> 00:24:46.067
[belching]

408
00:24:48.236 --> 00:24:50.739
[belching softly]
Excuse me.

409
00:24:54.242 --> 00:24:56.244
[audience chattering]

410
00:24:59.414 --> 00:25:02.209
-[dragon hissing]
-[audience exclaiming]

411
00:25:04.503 --> 00:25:05.921
[audience gasps]

412
00:25:05.962 --> 00:25:07.964
Wow.

413
00:25:08.006 --> 00:25:09.758
[applause]

414
00:25:13.094 --> 00:25:15.096
[dragon hissing]

415
00:25:21.436 --> 00:25:23.605
[squealing]

416
00:25:35.116 --> 00:25:36.493
[dragon thuds]

417
00:25:36.535 --> 00:25:38.745
[both laughing]

418
00:25:42.374 --> 00:25:44.209
[both sighing]

419
00:25:44.251 --> 00:25:46.211
Aerion. he's all smiles
and chivalry

420
00:25:46.253 --> 00:25:47.921
as long as
his father's watching.

421
00:25:47.963 --> 00:25:50.257
I saw Prince Maekar's chair
was empty.

422
00:25:50.298 --> 00:25:51.508
He left Ashford this morning

423
00:25:51.550 --> 00:25:53.260
to search for the rest
of his misbegats.

424
00:25:53.301 --> 00:25:55.554
Misbegats?
W-Which are those?

425
00:25:55.595 --> 00:25:58.640
His heir. Daeron.
and the youngest.

426
00:25:58.682 --> 00:26:00.725
They departed Summerhall
together a few days ago.

427
00:26:00.767 --> 00:26:02.769
but never reached Ashford.

428
00:26:03.895 --> 00:26:06.106
There's rumors going about
that the boys are dead.

429
00:26:06.147 --> 00:26:08.441
Though most like Daeron.

430
00:26:08.483 --> 00:26:09.985
he's probably just drunk again.

431
00:26:12.487 --> 00:26:14.072
Little wonder
Maekar's been walking around

432
00:26:14.114 --> 00:26:15.865
like someone pissed
in his swan pie.

433
00:26:15.907 --> 00:26:18.201
He's probably just worried
about his sons.

434
00:26:18.243 --> 00:26:19.953
Seven know why.

435
00:26:19.995 --> 00:26:24.666
Daeron's a sot.
Aerion's just vain and cruel.

436
00:26:24.666 --> 00:26:26.501
The third's so useless.
they were gonna ship him off

437
00:26:26.501 --> 00:26:28.169
to a citadel
to make a maester of him.

438
00:26:28.169 --> 00:26:30.839
-And the youngest--
-Ser! Ser Duncan!
You have to come!

439
00:26:30.880 --> 00:26:33.300
-Aerion's hurting her.
-Hurting who?

440
00:26:33.341 --> 00:26:35.343
[crowd clamoring]

441
00:26:36.886 --> 00:26:38.680
-Stay back!
-[clamoring continues]

442
00:26:38.680 --> 00:26:40.849
[dog barking]

443
00:26:40.890 --> 00:26:42.892
[screaming]

444
00:26:46.354 --> 00:26:48.565
-[bone snapping]
-[screaming]

445
00:26:53.903 --> 00:26:56.114
[Tanselle continues screaming]

446
00:26:58.617 --> 00:27:00.201
-[grunting]
-[soldier] Hold still!

447
00:27:00.201 --> 00:27:01.286
Hold on!

448
00:27:05.248 --> 00:27:07.250
[Dunk breathing heavily]

449
00:27:09.961 --> 00:27:11.212
[spitting]

450
00:27:22.641 --> 00:27:25.268
Why did you throw your life
away for this whore?

451
00:27:27.187 --> 00:27:28.772
She's scarcely worth it.

452
00:27:31.024 --> 00:27:32.150
She's a traitor.

453
00:27:33.902 --> 00:27:35.695
The dragon ought never lose.

454
00:27:40.492 --> 00:27:41.910
Nothing more to say?

455
00:27:49.167 --> 00:27:51.795
[sniffling]
You've loosened
one of my teeth.

456
00:27:54.964 --> 00:27:57.175
So. we'll start
by breaking out
all of yours.

457
00:27:57.217 --> 00:27:58.551
[grunting]

458
00:27:58.593 --> 00:28:00.762
[shouting]

459
00:28:06.434 --> 00:28:09.270
[muffled shouting]

460
00:28:09.270 --> 00:28:11.731
[Egg] No! Don't touch him!

461
00:28:11.773 --> 00:28:13.942
-Ah...
-[Dunk] You stupid boy!

462
00:28:13.983 --> 00:28:15.860
Hold your tongue
or they'll hurt you.

463
00:28:15.902 --> 00:28:17.278
-No. they won't.
-[Raymun] Watch out. please.

464
00:28:17.320 --> 00:28:19.280
-Excuse me.
-If they do. they'll
answer to my father.

465
00:28:19.322 --> 00:28:20.615
Let go of him!

466
00:28:20.657 --> 00:28:22.909
Wate. Yorkel.
do as I say.

467
00:28:25.453 --> 00:28:28.998
You impudent little rat.
What's happened to your hair?

468
00:28:29.040 --> 00:28:32.460
I cut it off. brother.
I didn't want to look like you.

469
00:28:33.670 --> 00:28:36.881
[♪ dramatic choral music
playing]

470
00:28:43.596 --> 00:28:45.807
♪♪

471
00:28:55.734 --> 00:28:58.945
[♪ dramatic choral music
continues playing]
